==English==

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|exhibit||}}  (''transitive'')
# To [[display]] or [[show]] for others to see, especially at an [[exhibition]] or [[contest]]
#: ''He wanted to '''exhibit''' his baseball cards.''
# To [[demonstrate]]
#: ''The players '''exhibited''' great skill.''
# To [[submit]] [[evidence]] to a [[court]]
#: ''I now '''exhibit''' this bloody hammer.''

{{en-infl-reg-consonant|exhibit||}}  (''intransitive'')
# To display publically
#: ''Will you be '''exhibiting''' this year?''

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# An instance of [[exhibiting]] or something [[exhibited]]
# A public showing; an [[exhibition]]
#: ''The museum's new '''exhibit''' is drawing quite a crowd.''
# An article [[formally]] introduced as evidence in a court
#: '''''Exhibit'''-A is this photograph of the corpse.''

